 in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"grp1__a1.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1__a1.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp1__a2.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1__a2.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp1__a3.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1__a3.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp1_mku.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp1_mku.rds\"\n    },\n    \"grp2__b1.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2__b1.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp2__b2.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2__b2.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp2__b3.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2__b3.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"grp2_mku.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"grp2_mku.rds\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_961k2xLdQZRc5eQ0ELnW9TK3", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. List the files in the workspace to identify the RDS files available for processing.\\n2. Load the RDS files into R, concatenate them into a single tibble, and save the concatenated tibble as 'output/df_mku_split.rds'.\\n3. Pivot the concatenated tibble wider based on the 'metric' column.\\n4. Calculate 'mCpG' using the formula 'mCpG = numCs / coverage', excluding rows where 'coverage' is zero.\\n5. Group the data by 'sample' and 'chr', compute the mean 'mCpG' for each group.\\n6. Save the results to 'output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv'.\\n7. Verify the existence of 'output/mean_mcpg_split.tsv' and call submit_done(success=true) if it exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation